FBIS3-35620 "drsov020_f_94003" FBIS-SOV-94-020 Document Type:Daily Report 31 Jan 1994 National Affairs Meshkov Holds News Conference on Victory Crimea To Remain Part of Ukraine LD3001224294 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 2155 GMT 30 Jan 94 LD3001224294 Kiev UNIAR Language: Ukrainian Article Type:BFN [Text] Simferopol, 30 Jan -- Yuriy Meshkov, the chairman of the Republican Party of Crimea, who won today's presidential election, held a news conference this afternoon at the Russian-speaking Movement of Crimea headquarters. He said that a referendum in favor of Crimea's independence within a union with other states will mean that the Republic of Crimea will return to the Constitution of 6 May 1992, according to Article Nine of which the Republic of Crimea remains a part of Ukraine on a confederation basis.
